#Text=Wikinews discusses the H1N1 pandemic with the CDC
#Text=Friday , November 6 , 2009
#Text=The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention ( CDC ) is a US government agency .
#Text=In an interview with Wikinews , Jeff Dimond , a member of the Division of Media Relations for the CDC , answered a few question regarding the current situation of the H1N1 swine flu pandemic .

#Text=The CDC reported that during week 42 ( October 18 – 24 ) of this year , the swine flu activity increased in the United States with 19 confirmed deaths by swine flu , while week 43 ( Oct. 25 – 31 ) faced 15 confirmed deaths .
#Text=( ( Wikinews ) ) How does the CDC feel the media has handled the H1N1 flu pandemic ?
#Text=Jeff Dimond : Media coverage has been quite good .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) What measures are the CDC taking to combat the swine flu ?
#Text=JD : Public health information is being distributed nationwide , scientists worked hard to identify the H1N1 virus and produce a vaccine in record time .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) What areas around the world are affected most by the swine flu ?
#Text=JD :
#Text=This is a question for the WHO ( World Health Organization ) .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) Are the current anti-flu vaccines effective and how sufficient is the current supply ?
#Text=JD : All current anti-flu vaccines are effective .
#Text=Manufacturers are producing doses as fast as possible .
#Text=Spot shortages may occur , but there is not an overall shortage of vaccine .
#Text=For the most severe cases , a drug called Peramivir has been authorized for emergency use by the FDA .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) How can one avoid infection and how deadly is this disease ?
#Text=JD : Proper hand sanitation and avoidance of individuals who have flu-like symptoms is the best way to avoid becoming ill .
#Text=To date more than 1000 Americans have died from LABORATORY CONFIRMED cases of H1N1 and of those 129 are under the age of 18 .
#Text=The most at-risk populations are pregnant women , younger people in the 18 – 49 age group and those with other complicating conditions such as asthma , COPD , diabetes and morbid obesity .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) What efforts have the CDC made to insure vaccines are available for those with no or poor health-care ?
#Text=JD : Distribution of vaccine is up to the state health departments .
#Text=CDC is not a regulatory agency .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) If someone suspects they have swine flu what would the best course of action be ?
#Text=JD : They should seek medical attention .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) When will the swine flu die down and cease being a pandemic ?
#Text=JD : No idea .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) Besides the CDC , what other entities , governmental and private , are involved in stopping this disease and how ?
#Text=JD : All public health and medical agencies with a stake in H1N1 are cooperating to control the spread of H1N1 .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) Is there a significant risk of H1N1 mutating and becoming more deadly ?
#Text=JD :
#Text=Flu viruses are unpredictable so there is no way of answering this question .
#Text=The CDC is constantly monitoring these viruses .
